System Analysis
Data Analysis
                The proposed Supply Monitoring with Construction Development Monitoring is highly data-driven, relying on structured entities and well-defined relationships to ensure the integrity and consistency of information across modules. The analysis of system data centers on identifying the key entities, their attributes, and the relationships that interconnect them.

Entity Identification:
Users – stores user account details, login credentials, and role assignments 
(Admin, 1 Super admin).
Projects – contains essential project information such as project title, location, number of units, duration, and status.
Materials – manages the global inventory of construction materials, including material name, category, quantity, unit, and acquisition date.
Construction Reports – records daily progress reports for each project, containing report date, status, remarks, proof images, and used materials during the creation of the progress.
Report Material Usage – a junction entity that connects daily reports with the materials used, including quantities consumed and deduction status.
Project Checklists – manages project milestones and task completion indicators for progress monitoring.

